# NC Program Generator — Development Rules

## Core principles
- Safety first. Treat every G/M code related change as machine-impacting.
- Prioritize working behavior and correctness over explanations.
- Keep responses concise and result-focused unless detail is requested.

## Change guardrails
- Diff-first: present targeted edits, avoid full-file rewrites unless required.
- Ask before changing proprietary calculation logic or G/M code definitions.

## User preference defaults
- Prioritize implementation over explanation unless the user explicitly asks for details.
- Prefer clear Japanese placeholder naming in templates and replace maps.
- Follow "report only when needed": skip routine completion reports when the user says reporting is unnecessary.
- Do not append post-implementation checklists unless explicitly requested.
- Token management: if estimated consumption will be excessive (e.g., very long code or bulk file processing), stop and propose alternatives.

## Managed files
- Shell: `index.html`
- Assets: `assets/style.css`, `assets/data.js`, `assets/app.js`, `assets/i18n.js`, `assets/operator-hints.js`（オペレーター向け注意書きのみ編集可）
- Templates under `テンプレート/`: `data_template_*.js`

## Project-specific knowledge
- Tonbo (`workType === "Tonbo"`) templates and build tooling are discontinued; `generateGCode` rejects that work type with a clear message.
- M408 = machining completion signal sent to external equipment (NCL044 only)
- M61 = machining completion signal (NCL012 only)
- NCL085 has no machining completion signal; output is intentionally empty
- G/M code roles differ by machine; do not assume standard behavior
- Template placeholders use `{{key}}` and are resolved at generation time
- Internal style `Yose` outputs machining path/block, but `YoseRelay` is calculation-only for first-process ID depth
- `YoseRelay` first-process ID depth formula: totalLength - secondProcessIDDepth - ((partnerDia/2 - machinedDia/2) / tan(taperAngle)) + 1
